<dl id="n54121c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54121c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54121c"> 121(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lights, beacons / for whimsical mistress, <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54121c"><li>FW 52.21 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n54121c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n54121c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54121c">MS BL 47476a-172</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:365 <a name="cd10" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n54121c">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">In a fit of boredom she <font color="green">[the king&apos;s mistress]</font> did not smile for a week and in order to amuse her the king ordered to be <mark>lighted on the hilltops the flares of wolf bones which served as a signal</mark> to the vassal princes to rally to repel an attack by barbarians. <small> Carl Crow, <a name="CCMK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CCMK"><cite title="source">Master Kung. The Story of Confucius</cite></a> (Sep 1937) 86</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
